For the book by Simon Wiesenthal, see . 
<b>The Sunflower</b> (<language wordnetid="106282651" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../708/14708.xml">
Italian</link></language>
: <it>Il Girasole</it>) was a political alliance of two <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../372/396372.xml">
Italian</link> leftist parties for the <group_action wordnetid="101080366" confidence="0.8">
<general_election wordnetid="100182435" confidence="0.8">
<election wordnetid="100181781" confidence="0.8">
<vote wordnetid="100182213" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../845/2289845.xml">
2001 general election</link></psychological_feature>
</act>
</event>
</vote>
</election>
</general_election>
</group_action>
, namely:<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../307/792307.xml">
Federation of the Greens</link></party>
 (<it>Federazione dei Verdi</it>)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

 <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../711/788711.xml">
Italian Democratic Socialists</link></party>
 (<it>Socialisti Democratici Italiani</it>)</entry>
</list>
</p>
<p>

It was founded to benefit from the proportional list system employed; however, they received too few votes to benefit from their alliance (they did manage to enter Olive Garden on the common list of the <party wordnetid="108256968" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../899/725899.xml">
Olive Tree</link></party>
, however), and it was disbelted soon afterwards.</p>

